# Progress & docs harness (schema v1)

## Design principle

- **Pulse (volatile)**: [docs/dev/PROGRESS.md](../../docs/dev/PROGRESS.md) — current status, blockers, next action.
- **Contracts (stable)**: PRD / TECH_DESIGN / ARCHITECTURE — change only when decisions change.
- **Door / nav**: README / AGENTS — change only when how-to-use or agent map drifts.
- Do **not** treat every small code tweak as a reason to rewrite all docs.

## Source of truth

| Topic | File | Update when |
|-------|------|-------------|
| Current pulse + next | docs/dev/PROGRESS.md | Every session with real progress |
| What / acceptance | docs/spec/PRD.md | Requirements change |
| Stack / APIs | docs/dev/TECH_DESIGN.md | Tech decisions change |
| Module slices + verify | docs/dev/ARCHITECTURE.md | Modules added/removed/renamed |
| Agent short nav | docs/dev/AGENTS.md | Nav/commands/rules drift |
| Human how-to | README.md | Install/use/share flow changes |

New chat: read **docs/dev/PROGRESS.md** first (see docs/dev/AGENTS.md). Do not dump full PRD/TECH into context unless the task needs them.

## When to update PROGRESS.md (mandatory)

Same session, if any of: code/config/docs changed; verify passed; git commit; user confirmed/rejected a feature; blocker appears/clears.

Skip only for pure Q&A with zero repo changes.

Keep updates **short**: Snapshot + Recent (1 line) + Next. Do not pad.

## Status legend

| Mark | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `[ ]` | Not started |
| `[~]` | Implemented; verify or sign-off pending |
| `[x]` | Verified |
| `[!]` | Blocked — note in Snapshot |

## Minimum PROGRESS update (when required)

1. Snapshot — phase, Git (`git log -1 --oneline`), blockers
2. Module rows — stay aligned with ARCHITECTURE (no need to invent new modules)
3. Recent changes — one dated line; keep last ~5
4. Next — one copy-paste prompt (or “V1 done / optional next”)

## Do NOT update every session

- PRD / TECH_DESIGN / CONTENT — unless product or tech decision changed
- README / AGENTS — unless entry instructions or nav became wrong
- Rewriting the same “all modules [x]” table with no new facts

## End-of-session gate

Before final reply (only if this session changed the repo):

- [ ] PROGRESS reflects reality (phase, Next, Recent)
- [ ] Git hash in Snapshot if a commit happened this session
- [ ] README/AGENTS touched **only** if user-facing or nav facts changed
